				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you delay frames by the repeating pattern 16, 17, 17, 16, 17, 17 ...  then the average is exactly 16.666666... msec between frames. Moral of the story: regardless of timing granularity, you can <em>on average</em> get a delay to any precision you like. You could have the average delay be exactly 16.1234567 msec, even though you can only delay by whole milliseconds.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

