						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If you do not do one of those two things, and you hold a steady 60 Hz framerate... your sound will break, probably in the form of buffer overflow (since you'll be producing audio faster than you're outputting it) which will result in a "crack" or break in the audio every few seconds -- the severity of which can differ depending on how you're streaming audio.</div>
<br />Wouldn't the sound driver block if the sound buffer was full? And it blocking would be exactly what you need to slow graphics down when needed.</div>

