					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- That's why I asked about the number of cycles per second. If you take the PPU timing, we have 341/3 cycles per line, 262 lines, 60 frames per second, making exactly 1786840 cycles per second. This is my reference. If you take the CPU timing, we have a different number.</div>
<br />
<br />Yeah -- which is why you can't have 60 FPS if you want the right APU/CPU frequency.  You need to do the ~60.1 FPS
<br />
<br />NTSC CPU clock = 1789772.727272
<br />
<br />NTSC frame = 262 scanlines * 341 cycles per scanline / 3 PPU cycs per CPU cycle = 29780.666667 CPU cycles per frame
<br />
<br />1789772.727272 / 29780.6666667 = ~60.09847  FPS
<br />
<br />
<br />Gotta go... will respond more when I get back</div>

